<div class="bsf_rt_user_manual">
	<br><label class="bsf_rt_page_title" for="howtouse">How to Use? </label><br><br>
	<b>Step 1</b> : Go to the <i>General Settings</i> Tab and select the Words Per Minute ,
	         and Post types on which you want to display the Read time and progress bar. <br><br>
	<b>Step 2</b> : Go to the <i>Read Time</i> Tab and select the Show Estimated Read time on option , and the Read time position and Prefix and the Postfix of the Readtime to Display. <br><br>
	<b>Step 3</b> : Go to the <i>Progress Bar</i> Tab and select the position to display the Progress Bar ,also select the style eother Normal or gradient and select the colors for it accordingly and select the Thickeness of progress bar as per your need. <br><br>
	<b>Step 4</b> : Now you are Done with Settings and can now see the reading Time and the Progress Bar as per your selected options !!<br><br><br>
	<b> Shortcode : [read_meter]</b> <br><br>
		You can also display the reading time wherever you want by using this shortcode , You just need to copy it and paste it in any content of Post or Page.
</div>